- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about speech recognition and acoustic modeling, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with audio data and its processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a deep neural network model with differentiable pooling operators. 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing) is a possible category as the paper deals with processing of speech signals. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes a novel technique for unsupervised acoustic model adaptation using deep neural networks.
